high_concept: Programmatic API-based cloud storage security via distributed data concealment.
name: CryptoMove
product_desc:
CryptoMove is programmatic API-based distributed file storage security. Its core continuous concealment technology cryptographically mutates stored data content and re-encrypts moving file parts around the distributed data store.  Because of this dynamic approach, no attacker can identify data of interest, and sensitive data can safely go to the cloud.  

CryptoMove will make all data-at-rest encryption a thing of the past. CryptoMove's dynamic security approach loses attackers in a sea of obfuscation. Unlocks enterprise movement of sensitive files to the cloud. Securely stores files in AWS (or local networks or other clouds). Best way to secure encryption keys to legacy static data-at-rest encryption technologies.

We're working with multiple pilot customers who want a simple programmatic white-label API to store sensitive user or other data backups via CryptoMove in the cloud.

FAQ:  https://goo.gl/3xXLV1.  Bootstrapped development to date.

markets: [{'tag_type': 'MarketTag', 'id': 2, 'display_name': 'Biotechnology', 'angellist_url': 'https://angel.co/biotechnology', 'name': 'biotechnology'}, {'tag_type': 'MarketTag', 'id': 2386, 'display_name': 'Dietary Supplements', 'angellist_url': 'https://angel.co/dietary-supplements', 'name': 'dietary supplements'}, {'tag_type': 'MarketTag', 'id': 2540, 'display_name': 'Quantified Self', 'angellist_url': 'https://angel.co/quantified-self', 'name': 'quantified self'}, {'tag_type': 'MarketTag', 'id': 154033, 'display_name': 'Quantified Health', 'angellist_url': 'https://angel.co/quantified-health', 'name': 'Quantified Health'}]
product_desc:
We are DoubleBlinded, Inc., a new company dedicated to quality, safe, scientific self experimentation and citizen-science. Our goal is to apply scientific method and industry best practices to self-monitoring and health logging. We view ourselves as a keystone to the Quantified Self movement and our long term goal is to improve quality of life using science.

We are organizing our first ever group double-blinded study, available beginning December 1st, 2015 and lasting 28 days. We send you a one month kit to trial L-Theanine. You will receive four pill organizers, one for each week of the month. Each week may be either placebo or 200mg of L-Theanine and you will not know which it is. At the end of each day you will fill out a short survey with a few questions evaluating the effects of the pills. At the end of the 28 days you will see your results - including charts comparing your evaluations of actual L-Theanine to placebo - along with the combined anonymized results of the group.

high_concept: Blood Testing Products for Brain Disease
name: MSDx
product_desc:
MSDx is a personalized medicine company developing blood testing products for monitoring neurodegeneration in brain diseases. These products provide the neurologists with critical data that can be useful in diagnosis, monitoring, and assessing therapeutics response. We call our patented blood test panel WINDOW INTO THE BRAIN. 

In 2013, MSDx’s first patent was issued for its WINDOW INTO THE BRAIN technology, describing methods of detecting a neurological condition via analysis of circulating phagocytes. The WINDOW INTO THE BRAIN test panel offers a real-time view of pathological processes and disease activity in the brain. Often referred to as a “non-invasive brain biopsy,” it includes regulatory, demyelination, neurodegenerative, and leukocyte transmigration biomarkers. MSDx’s assays can be tested individually or as a panel. Though initially focused on Multiple Sclerosis (MS), this technology may be applied to other neurological disorders such as Parkinson’s disease(PD)..

name: Seateroo

The Seateroo app offers a marketplace for airline seat swaps. Pre- or post-boarding, air travelers may check the Seateroo marketplace for current buy or sell orders, make an offer, post a new order, negotiate price, and make or receive electronic payment. With a limited inventory of preferred airline seats, Seateroo helps users swap for a preferred seat either prior to or after boarding. In addition, by enabling passengers to set the price for a seat swap, Seateroo helps other users monetize a seat preferred by another passenger. 

Seateroo will expand the inventory of preferred seats for passengers unable to purchase a preferred seat at the time of purchase. Seateroo will also expand the time window for passengers to acquire a preferred seat. Lastly, Seateroo will enable passengers to access preferred seats "on-demand" after boarding a flight, such as the desire to move away from a crying child or towards a friend or colleague. 

Seateroo is scheduled to launch in December 2015.

name: TWAIN
product_desc:
We have developed an Artificial Intelligence Engine that uses Speech Recognition to deliver language lessons as if you were talking to a real human teacher.

There are 1.2 billion people learning a foreign language in the world. Some 800 million want to learn English.

In Asia English teaching apps account for $1 Billion in revenue, with the top three countries being China, Korea and Japan

Current technology language solutions schedule a student with a teacher online or via Skype for a video conference. The disadvantages to this method is scalability and quality of teachers.

Over the past 12 months we have developed a purely software driven alternative, a multi-lingual Artificial Intelligence Engine that uses Speech Recognition and TTS (Text-to-Speech), to create a similar experience as if it was a real human teacher.

Our software driven approach is scalable and delivers consistent quality teaching at a fraction of the cost of competitors offerings.

name: Young Mind Interactive
product_desc:
Young Mind Interactive, is a developer and publisher of educational games, eBooks and digital learning tools. We create engaging, effective teaching applications to enhance the learning experience in the classroom and home learning environment. Our products are designed for use in today’s classrooms on mobile devices, laptops, desktops and projected interactive screens, providing a hands-on learning experience while enhancing the learning experience at school and beyond.

Our goal is to provide students and educators with the newest teaching tools for the modern classroom. To do so, we consult educators and education experts throughout the development process in order to produce games that are effective at providing a working knowledge and understanding of the topics covered. We are continuously exploring subjects and developing new apps to engage students of all ages, and we also provide customized apps to address specific topics and curricula for clients in Education.
